  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n```\r\nWARN Eth1 endpoint is not synced\r\nCRIT Couldn't connect to any eth1 node.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThose two messages together is kind of confusing to me.  One implies that the endpoint isn't synced and the other implies that it isn't reachable at all.  It seems like the WARN message should be suppressed if the CRIT message is true, as the beacon node can't know the state of the endpoint if it is unable to connect to it.",
